        <abstract> 
<p>Praise for <hi rend="italic">Movement in plants</hi>.</p>  
<p>He thinks G. A. Chatin, whom CD quotes [p. 389], is mistaken about movement of conifer leaves. Cites his own paper ["Relations between morphology and physiology in the leaves of certain conifers", <hi rend="italic">J. Linn. Soc. Lond. (Bot.)</hi> 17 (1880): 547–52].</p> 
